## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/world-map.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Use `Design.md` (World Map section) and `Logic.md` (map markers, layers, flyouts) for interaction detail.

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/world-map.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/app/components/layerData.ts` | Country tier per layer, tier colors, metadata |
| `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx` | Flag helpers for map/UI |
| `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` | `MapLayerOption`, `VpnFeatureType` |
| `src/app/components/ui/*` | shadcn primitives if used |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Marker list and coordinates are defined in `WorldMap.tsx`; keep in sync with `layerData` country coverage where applicable.
- Basemap/tile URL and Leaflet integration must remain functional; follow `Logic.md` for marker click behavior.
- Changing layer keys requires alignment with `layerData.ts` and `MapLayerOption`.

## Patterns to Follow

- Stateless w.r.t. global truth: receive all state from `App` via props; emit changes via callbacks only.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT duplicate data or helpers from `layerData.ts`, `flagComponents.tsx`, or Figma `imports` — import and compose.
- Do NOT modify `App.tsx` or other features without explicit approval and doc updates.
- Do NOT add routes — none are defined for this feature.
- Do NOT change tier/layer semantics without updating `/docs/features/world-map.md` and `regulatory-data.md` / `layerData.ts` first.
